ure is in comparison rules, not infrastructure interaction.","test_description":"Test semver comparison function with representative cases (1.2.3->2.0.0 breaking, 1.2.3->1.3.0 non-breaking, pre-release edge cases) and assert breaking flag is correct.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.92,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is an orchestration contract between semver decision logic, PR service caller, and report/output module. Unit tests on any one component can miss incorrect handoff.","test_description":"Execute scanner orchestration with a fixture that triggers a major bump; verify PR client is not invoked and output/report contains a breaking-change review flag with dependency details.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
